Create your own note to cherish through various productivity tools
Tap productivity tools icon to use handwriting recognition and insert the result as text or image

Select the formula match icon from the productivity tools pop-up, and enter a handwritten formula. Then the formula you have entered will be recognised and the results displayed at the top. You can search for solutions to the formula using the Wolfram Alpha search engine or insert the typed formula into the note

Select the shape match icon from the productivity tools pop-up and draw a shape or line. These shapes will automatically be corrected and completed. You can delete lines that stick out by rubbing over the area with your finger or a pen

Tap handwriting-to-text icon in the productivity tools pop-up, then the words you write will be recognised and converted into text. You can correct the result using the 4 navigation keys and the backspace key

Tapping the screen with two fingers and then swiping them in opposite directions is called pinch zoom. When you have zoomed in using pinch zoom in Create/Edit mode, you can pan by swiping the screen with two fingers
